column41: Would you like to make more?
column42: If you change your mind, let me know!

column38: Here for the job, are you? Then there's no need for pleasantries. Show me your work.
column39:
Let me see here...
Hm... I believe this will do. Here is the payment promised.
column40: I have nothing more to say until you've completed my order.

column38: Ah, you must be the adventurer the guild said they would send. I have been ever so eagerly awaiting your arrival. Might you have the delivery on your person?
column39: Excellent. You are to be commended, good <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lady<Else/>sir</If>. I believe this should be sufficient remuneration for your services.
column40: Well, then. Take your time. I do not wish to see you sacrifice quality if it only means I save a few bells. You know where I will be.

column38: Your arrival here this <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>night<Else/>morn</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>night</If></If> was foretold in the stars. You have something to...deliver, don't you?
column39: Ah, yes, your success was never in question. The universe is pleased and grants you your reward.
column40: Shhh. Hush, now. The Spinner has decreed your path. Craft away, my child. Craft away.
column41: But wait... What is this I sense? A desire to craft more?
column42: Could it be that the stars were wrong? Bah! I have a feeling you will be back, my child, and I shall be here waiting when you do.
column43: A thousand thanks, my child! Until our paths cross again!

column38: Have you completed my request? I know you adventurers are the busy sort, but I, too, have deadlines to meet.
column39: A fine display of synthesis. I must extend to you my admiration and gratitude...in the form of a reward, of course.
column40: Well, may the Builder watch over your endeavors. But remember, Black Rabbit Traders <Emphasis>also</Emphasis> appreciate promptness.
column41: Now, if it is further employment that you seek, I would be willing to make you a similar offer for more of the same item. What say you?
column42: Very well. You know where to find me, should you come to your senses.

column38: So it is you that accepted my unit's request. Very well, then. Let us see what you have brought us.
column39: Yes, yes... This appears to meet Wood Wailer standards. You have my unit's thanks, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. Let me prepare your reward forthwith.
column40: My men and I require those supplies immediately. Every moment you tarry puts us in danger of being unprepared for an attack.

column38: From the Adventurers' Guild, are you? Very good, very good.
column39:
Finished, are we? Let me take a look.
Yes... Yes... Very good. Very good, indeed. You have done a fine job today, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. My superiors at the Consortium will be pleased, to say the least.
column40: The Brugaire Consortium is known for the expediency with which it fills its orders. If you refuse to complete the items I have requested, I will simply hire another adventurer to do my bidding. Gods know there are more than enough of you running around this city to choose from.
column41: And, I believe they would be even <Emphasis>more</Emphasis> pleased if I were to return to the warehouses with a healthy surplus of the requested goods. You seem competent enough in your chosen trade. Would you consider contributing a few more whacks of the proverbial hammer in service of Brugaire?
column42: I see. Off with you then. I am a busy man, and my clients are waiting.
column43: You have served the Consortium well. I shall duly note your contributions in my log. Good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>night<Else/>day</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>night</If></If>, then.

column38: I thank you very much for accepting my request. I fancy myself a decent craftswoman, yet there are some fields in which I have found employing the services of another can often prove most fortuitous for both parties.
column39: Wonderful! Your reputation for quality proceeds you. I shall remember you if I happen to require assistance again.
column40: Have you completed my request? I know you adventurers are the busy sort, but I, too, have deadlines to meet.

column38: Hmph. You don't have the look of a crafts<If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If>. Then again, I am not paying for looks. Make me what I have requested and all parties shall be satisfied.
column39: I find your work more than satisfactory. Let me thank you. May our paths cross again.
column40: I await your completion of the task I requested.

column38: You the <If(PlayerParameter(4))>lass<Else/>lad</If> the Adventurers' Guild sent to do my synthesis? I'm H'rhanbolo, captain of the <Emphasis>Ice Princess</Emphasis>─third fastest trading ship in all of Limsa.
column39: Everything seems to be in order; a fine job, if I do say so myself. You ever think about hanging up your adventurer's britches, let me know. There might be a place for you on the Princess.
column40: The Navigator did well to guide you here, but don't think she'll save you if my order isn't ready soon.
column41: But before you trade in your land legs, could a lady ask one last favor? Those items I requested...might you be able to craft a few more? There's coin to be had, don't you worry.
column42: That's unfortunate. My crew and I set sail soon, and I've never been one for waiting. Perhaps next time, then.
column43: Such fine work! You are either a master at your craft, or a master at finding someone who's a master at their craft to make you look like a master at your craft. Either way, the Princess gets get supplies, and you get your reward. Everyone wins!

column38: Where in Thal's bowels have you been? There's work to be done. Come on, come on, get to it! Commerce and industry wait for no Lalafell! Especially when that Lalafell is Master Gegeruju.
column39: Finally done, are we? Couldn't remember if you were quenching or cross-stitching, is that it? Hand it over, then! Pleasure doing business and all that!
column40: Are you getting to it, or do I have to get on you!?
column41: Oh, wait. Where are you going? I wasn't finished. Would a <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> of your means be interested in whipping up a few more of those fine items? The master likes to see that he's always prepared.
column42: No get-up-and-go in your blood? Pity... Then again, the master has <Emphasis>other</Emphasis> means of getting what he needs.
column43: Excellent. Master Gegeruju always says, why have one of anything when you can have a dozen.

column38: Good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>afternoon<Else/>evening</If></If>, adventurer. Handing in or picking up? One moment, please.
column39: Handing in? Sign here, please. Thank you, and have a nice day. Next!
column40: I cannot sign off on your contract until you complete the order. Next!
column41: If your business is not pressing, might Ashgana's Exporters persuade you to extend your contract? You will be rightly recompensed.
column42: Not willing, eh? Very good. Sign here, please. Next!
column43: Handing in surplus? Sign here, please. Thank you, and have a wonderful day. Next!

column38: This <Emphasis>stripling</Emphasis> is who they send in answer to my summons? I trust you understand the <Emphasis>importance</Emphasis> of this work?
column39: Well, I suppose this is <Emphasis>adequate</Emphasis>. You may return to your so–called <Emphasis>adventuring</Emphasis>.
column40: Let us not <Emphasis>mince</Emphasis> words here. The Seventy-seven Caravans requires <Emphasis>perfection</Emphasis>. Pure and simple. Your <Emphasis>reputation</Emphasis> is at stake here, as is <Emphasis>mine</Emphasis>. You are to begin <Emphasis>at once</Emphasis>.

column38: Well? You gonna hand it over, or just stand there gawpin'?
column39: Hmph. I s'pose this'll hafta do. You done what you came for. Off you trot.
column40: You waltzed in here empty-handed? I oughta box your ears, you cheeky git. Now start craftin' or start bleedin'. Your choice.

column38: Yes, and how may I help you? ...Oh! Oh, an adventurer! From that guild! Which one was it now? Ah, yes! The Adventurers' Guild! And why were you here again? Ah, the order!
column39: Er... Are you sure this is what I asked for? Whatever was I thinki─ Ah? Oh, no matter, I'm sure it will come to me! My thanks!
column40: Don't tell me you've forgotten to bring the order! My memory is like a steel trap, you see. Can't abide forgetfulness. Hm? Oh yes, the order! Did you bring it? No? Well then, craft away!
column41: Oh, but before you go off to wherever it is you adventurers go, might I ask that you make me some more? I have this sinking feeling I might just...er, misplace the ones you've already submitted.
column42: No? Oh... Well, I'm certain you have your reasons... Whatever they might be.
column43: Wonderful... I think. This <Emphasis>is</Emphasis> what I ordered, right?
